06 Jul 2020 23:39






So the DoA is just doing the job that the modern Foundation would do anyways? Having some terminals and lab equipment in the room with kid skeletons doesn't imply that they're containing or studying the thing any more than it implies that they are the organ's creators, especially considering the DoA's other articles.

Why include them in the piece at all if the article would work just as fine without them? It's like the article is trying to focus on two things; the Church's history of the mistreatment of children, and then the DoA trying to utilize a loyalty-generating anomaly for its own ends. It's way less punchy to have the piece be about one group doing a pretty bad thing (mind controlling its employees) with another group's pretty bad thing (dead child piano). It doesn't elaborate on the former at all and focuses on the latter for the punchline. It's defocusing itself trying to say  piece.







